author: David McCollum
title: Faulkner Roundup: CBC golf and St. Joseph volleyball
text:
Faulkner Roundup: CBC golf and St. Joseph volleyball Posted: October 8, 2015 - 7:06pm By David McCollum LOG CABIN STAFF WRITER 
With a fourth-place finish in the Central regional, the Central Baptist College golf team has qualified for the National Christian College Athletic Association’s national tournament. 
The tournament will be at Panama City, Fla. 
Dallas Baptist won the regional at Bartlesville, Okla., with an 888 total. Colorado Christian was second at 892, Oklahoma Wesleyan third at 894 and CBC third at 912. 
The Mustangs’ Austin Harmon tied for 
fifth. Cameron Reasor tied for 14th and Luke Cornett tied for 19th. 
ST. JOSEPH-CCS VOLLEYBALL 
St. Joseph toook a 25-19, 25-18, 21-25, 25-19 volleyball victory over Conway Christian on Tuesday at the St. Joseph Family Activity Center. 
Brianna Wells had 11 kills for St. Joseph (14-9, 7-3). Rachell Prall added nine kills. 
Maggie Baine was perfect on 23 serves and had two aces. Abby McKenna had 15 assists. Joanie Elsinger had four blocks and Emily Flake three. Tia Massa had 10 digs. 
“Too many missed serves but a cleaner game,” said coach Luke Davis. “We hit the ball well and took steps forward.”
